# Answer: $m \in[-6054 ;-2017]$.

## Solution:

Consider $f(x)=2018 \cdot \sqrt[5]{6.2 x-5.2}+2019 \cdot \log _{5}(4 x+1)+m-2020$.

On the domain of definition $D_{f}=\left(-\frac{1}{4} ;+\infty\right)$, the function is monotonically increasing, as the sum of monotonically increasing functions. The equation $f(x)=0$ has a unique solution. This solution will belong to the interval $[1 ; 6]$ if and only if,

$$
\left\{\begin{array} { l } 
{ f ( 1 ) \leq 0 , } \\
{ f ( 6 ) \geq 0 . }
\end{array} \Rightarrow \left\{\begin{array} { c } 
{ 2 0 1 8 + 2 0 1 9 + m - 2 0 2 0 \leq 0 } \\
{ 2 0 1 8 \cdot 2 + 2 0 1 9 \cdot 2 + m - 2 0 2 0 \geq 0 . }
\end{array} \Rightarrow \left\{\begin{array}{l}
m \leq-2017 \\
m \geq-6054
\end{array}\right.\right.\right.
$$

Let $b_{i}=\frac{1}{n-1+a_{i}}(i=1,2, \cdots, n)$, then $b_{i}<1$, and let $M=$ $\frac{1}{n-1} \sum_{j=1}^{n} \sum_{i \neq j} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{1-b_{j}(n-1)}$.

On one hand, $M=\frac{1}{n-1} \sum_{j=1}^{n} \sum_{i \neq j} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{1-b_{j}(n-1)}=\frac{1}{n-1} \sum_{j=1}^{n} \frac{(n-1)\left(1-\sum_{i \neq j} b_{i}\right)}{1-b_{j}(n-1)}$ (1).

On the other hand, $M=\frac{1}{n-1} \sum_{i=1}^{n} \sum_{j \neq i} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{1-b_{j}(n-1)}$
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\geqslant \frac{1}{n-1} \sum_{i=1}^{n}(n-1)^{2} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{\sum_{j \neq i}\left(1-b_{j}(n-1)\right)} \text { (Cauchy inequality) } \\
=\sum_{i=1}^{n} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{1-\sum_{j \neq i} b_{j}}>\sum_{i=1}^{n} \frac{1-b_{i}(n-1)}{b_{i}} \text { (here we use } \sum_{i=1}^{n} b_{i}>1 \text { ), }
\end{array}
$$

This leads to a contradiction, so $\sum^{n} b_{i} \leqslant 1$, which means the original proposition holds.

