Prove: Let $x=\tan \frac{A}{2}, y=\tan \frac{B}{2}, z=\tan \frac{C}{2}$, i.e., to prove
$$
\begin{array}{l}
u^{2}+v^{2}+w^{2} \\
\geqslant 2 w \frac{z}{\sqrt{1+z^{2}}}+2 u v \frac{y}{\sqrt{1+y^{2}}}+2 v w \frac{x}{\sqrt{1+x^{2}}}
\end{array}
$$

Notice that
$$
\begin{array}{l}
2 u v \frac{z}{\sqrt{1+z^{2}}}=2 z \cdot \frac{u}{\sqrt{y+z}} \cdot \frac{v}{\sqrt{z+x}} \\
\leqslant z\left(\frac{u^{2}}{y+z}+\frac{v^{2}}{z+x}\right) .
\end{array}
$$

Similarly, $2 w u \frac{y}{\sqrt{1+y^{2}}} \leqslant y\left(\frac{w^{2}}{x+y}+\frac{u^{2}}{y+z}\right)$,
$$
2 v w \frac{x}{\sqrt{1+x^{2}}} \leqslant x\left(\frac{v^{2}}{z+x}+\frac{w^{2}}{x+y}\right) \text {. }
$$

Adding the three inequalities, we get
the right side of equation (1)
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\leqslant \frac{x w^{2}+y w^{2}}{x+y}+\frac{y u^{2}+z u^{2}}{y+z}+\frac{x v^{2}+z v^{2}}{z+x} \\
=w^{2}+u^{2}+v^{2}
\end{array}
$$

Thus, equation (1) holds, and the proposition is proved.

